    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Culture, nationality, and styles of the Slavic linguistic and ethnic group that came from Asia in the third or second millennium BCE, spread steadily across eastern Europe, and played an important role in the Medieval world, particularly during the Slavic migrations.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
